title: For Sale/Trade:  JMCB 2003-DU Motorcycle CB radio/Intercom/Weather radio like brand new!
postcontent:
I have a JMCB 2003B-DU radio that is like new. I would like to trade it towards a Lever Action .357 rifle, maybe even a 30-30 in a Lever Action.
Its a 40 channel CB radio, an NOAA weather band radio, rider/passenger intercom and stereo music amplification from any MP3/I-pod/Portable-type music device, completely integrated together.


I might even have the bracket I used for it as well. The best price you'll find these on eBay is for $325 or more.

This one was on my bike since August, my birthday present to myself!

There's not a blemish on it anywhere and I'll include the antenna and mount I used. I didn't use any of the wiring that came with so it's all in the box, still wrapped up, and can pass for a brand new unit.

It's still under warranty and it's all yours for $350. 


-------------------
Also, Last and far from least is an awesome Baehr UltimaXL intercom that is amazing! This is the Cat-Daddy of them all. read any intercom comparison review you want to and you'll see they all compare themselves to Baehr. they admit they aren't as good, but the also tell you that they aren't as high priced. I had this hooked to my GPS, MP3, Stereo, the JMCB, and a Bluetooth device. Oh yeah, almost forgot to mention, it was hooked to both our helmets too! It's fully automatic so you never have to adjust anything once you have it set the way you want it. It turns on when the driver's helmet is plugged up and everything is set in priority. The volume adjusts itself as you go faster and you can carry on a normal conversation just like you are setting beside the person in a car. It does not use the hateful VOX that most intercoms do. The mic is always on so when you talk, the music automatically drops to a very low level and the other person hears every word you say as clear as a bell. Anyone that has ever slipped my spare helmet on and listened has been amazed. New, this goes for $1700 and you can buy it from me for $600 and that includes the headsets and mics, as well as some of the cables I made for it. It's a real steal and you wont be sorry. I'll include plenty of paperwork for it and it even has about 1 year of warranty left. I bought it brand new so it's only been on my bike. this will fit any bike, no matter what brand, Honda, Victory, Suzuki, Kawasaki, you name it! It take a few hours to install, and you'll love it. This made the ride for me and my bride a lot better. We could talk about where to eat, what we saw while we are riding, and she could warn me of deer close to the road if I didn't see them!

title: For Sale:  Taurus PT92 Stainless and Taurus .22 conversion kit
postcontent:
This gun is in great condition and has been cleaned immediately any time it was shot. The sear and a few other internals have received a light polish to produce a great SA and DA trigger. The gun will come with three 17 round magazines. I'm asking $425 for the PT92 and 3 mags. For an extra $25, I'll throw in a set of genuine Taurus rosewood grips. They are used, but in above average condition. For an extra $5, I'll include a Beretta "D" spring, which lightens up both the DA and SA trigger pulls. It takes less than 5 minutes to remove both grips and change out the main spring. 

I also have a Taurus brand .22 conversion kit. This kit has had less than 50 rounds fired through it. These kits come from the factory pretty tight, so I had to cycle it on the PT92 a few times with some lapping compound in the rail groove to get it to loosen up enough to cycle properly. I fired enough rounds through it to make certain it cycled properly, which it did. It was very accurate. This kit is a great way to rack up practice time on your PT92 at a much lower cost than shooting 9mm rounds. I'm asking $275 for the conversion kit. I will not sell the conversion separately until the pistol sells. 

I would much prefer to do a FTF transaction with another Kentucky resident. I'm in Hopkinsville, but would drive up to 60 miles to do the transaction. I will require to see a Kentucky drivers license.

 The 1994 Yamaha XJ600S Seca II engine has a displacement of 599-cubic centimeters, or 36.55-cubic inches. It is an in-line, four-cylinder, V-8, four-stroke engine.  Size and Frame

 The 1994 Yamaha XJ600S Seca II weighs 412.3 lbs. It's seat height is 30.3 inches, on the lowest setting. The frame is made of a steel tube double cradle.

 Fuel

 The 1994 Yamaha XJ600S Seca II has a fuel capacity of 17 liters and an average fuel consumption of 52 miles per gallon. The tank range of the Seca II is 165 miles.

 Tyres and Breaks

 The 1994 Yamaha XJ600S Seca II has two 320-mm discs on the front brakes and a single 245-millimeter disc on the rear brake. The front tire is a 110/80 x 17 while the rear tire is a 130/70 x 18.

title: For Sale:  U.S. REVOLVER CO. AUTOMATIC HAMMER - 1910-1935
postcontent:
needs grips and a new hammer spring

Revolver manufactured by Iver Johnson’s Arms & Cycle Works to be sold through wholesale trade. It was never listed in any Iver Johnson’s Arms & Cycle Works catalog, although it was listed in some European catalogs as original Iver Johnson product. Small frame .32 centerfire with 5 rounds cylinder capacity

u.s. revolver co. automatic small frame 32 S&W caliber serial number 3688 (no letter code) was manufactured in 1910, approx. 14,000 manufactured that year. these were made without a rebounding hammer and the only safety was the half cock (safety notch) do not carry with a round under the hammer. the free wheeling cylinder is the way they were made and is normal for this revolver. if timing is good (alignment of cylinder and barrel) and lock up tight (when hammer is down and trigger is to the rear) when in firing position, it should be safe with factory standard velocity 32 S&W ammo. just do not carry with a live cartridge under the hammer.
